Definition.WordDefinition:
Troglodytes \Trog`lo*dy"tes\, n. [NL. See {Troglodyte}.] 1. (Zo["o]l.) A genus of apes including the chimpanzee.
Note: The chimpanzee is now named {Pan troglodytes}., and its genus is {Pan}. [1913 Webster]
2. (Zo["o]l.) A genus of singing birds including the common wrens. [1913 Webster]
Troglodytes n : type genus of the Troglodytidae [syn: {genus Troglodytes}]
